The paper discusses the use of Educational Data Mining (EDM) techniques for analyzing data generated in Massive Open Online Courses (MOOCs). The tasks of knowledge tracing and peer feedback analysis are central to the paper, which suggests that the paper could fall under the categories of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper also discusses the use of sentiment analysis (cs.CY) and information retrieval (cs.IR) techniques, which further support the likelihood of these categories. Finally, the paper also discusses the use of social network analysis (cs.SI) for analyzing peer feedback, which could be another potential category.
